Authorities say more than 2,000 people have been affected. The Human Settlements MEC has visited the area to assess the situation. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports. #DStv403 DEELPAN - One person has died in floods in Deelpan, North West Province and over 170 families have been left homeless. Emergency officials say more people may need to be evacuated following downpours on Monday and they are remaining on high alert. Floods since January have affected thousands of people. Authorities say a task team has now been assembled to assist affected residents. * eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports.